blocks.text: The eight men's and women's squads for the inaugural season of The Hundred have been revealed.
After the latest replacements were announced on 2 July, here is how they look.
<italic>If this page is not displaying correctly, </italic><link><caption>please go here</caption><url href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/54646061" platform="highweb"/></link>

content.text: Marchant de Lange (replaces injured Wahab Riaz)
Hollie Armitage (passed fit following Covid & returns to squad)
Ben Duckett  (captain in absence of Jonny Bairstow)
Graeme White (while Jonny Bairstow is with England)
Harmanpreet Kaur (out for rest of competition with injury)
Joe Cracknell (replacement for Dan Lawrence while on international duty)
